\cb3         \cf2 \strokec2 <p>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3          Maj Gen Vijay Ranade\'a0is a former Indian Army officer, strategic affairs commentator, and independent researcher focusing on geopolitics, military history, national security, and India\'92s evolving strategic posture in the emerging global order. Drawing upon military experience and extensive engagement with strategic studies, his work explores the intersection of historical statecraft and contemporary security challenges.\cb1 \
\cb3 His research places particular emphasis on the Maratha era and the enduring lessons it offers in warfare, intelligence, maritime strategy, leadership, governance, and political innovation. Through historical analysis and contemporary commentary, he examines how the strategic experiences of early modern India continue to inform present-day defence policy, information warfare, and geopolitical competition.\cb1 \
\cb3 His broader areas of interest include:\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Indian military history and strategic culture\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Geopolitics and international relations\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Maritime security and Indo-Pacific strategy\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Information warfare and influence operations\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Defence reforms and national security policy\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Leadership, governance, and statecraft\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 His writings and analyses have also appeared in leading strategic and defence platforms, including CLAWS, USI, IDSA, and Bharat Shakti.\cb1 \
\cb3 The Cauldron of Thoughts\cb1 \
\cb3 Decoding Power, Strategy & the Lessons of History\cb1 \
\cb3 The Cauldron of Thoughts\'a0is a platform dedicated to examining geopolitics, military history, strategy, and India\'92s rise in a rapidly changing world order.\cb1 \
\cb3 From the forts of the Deccan to the contested waters of the Indo-Pacific, the blog explores how history, power, geography, technology, and political decision-making continue to shape national security and global affairs today.\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 The platform covers themes such as:\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Shivaji Maharaj and the Maratha strategy\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Military strategy and warfare\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Geopolitics and strategic affairs\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Maritime security and sea power\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Information warfare and strategic communication\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Leadership and historical lessons\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \'95 Counter-currents and unconventional perspectives\cf2 \strokec2 <br/>\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 The objective is simple \'97 to build a thinking community that approaches strategy not merely as history or theory, but as a living framework for understanding contemporary challenges and India\'92s long-term national interests.\cb1 \
\cb3 Engage, question, and contribute \'97 because strategic clarity is forged through debate and informed reflection.\cb1 \
